YsgardPlanar LanguageAlphabet: DethekRegions Spoken:  Ysgard and the Happy Hunting GroundsDificulty: 7Ysgard is the language of the nordic plane of the same name. It's derived from sylvan in the distant past, and like sylvan is a language of poetry and literature. Unlike sylvan poetry which focuses on the works of nature, Ysgardian writing focuses on heroic battles and individual valor, relishing the clash of steel most of all.The languages of the Centaurs and Jotun ( giants ) derived from Ysgardian. Illuski also derives from Ysgard having derived from both Jotun and from Ysgard directly, as it's people originally worshipped deities from this plane.